FT  14 OCT 92 / International Company News: ESFH revenue up 200% after six
months
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PATRICK BLUM
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   LISBON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
ESPIRITO Santo Financial Holding (ESFH), the Luxembourg-based banking arm of
Portugal's Espirito Santo group, reported a 200 per cent rise in operating
revenue to Dollars 132.6m for the first six months, compared with Dollars
41.6m in the same period in 1991.
The sharp rise in revenue is mainly due to the consolidation of the accounts
of Banco Espirito Santo e Comercial de Lisboa (BESCL), the Portuguese
commercial bank which was taken over by the group when it was fully
privatised last February. The Espirito Santo family owned the bank before
its nationalisation in 1975.
ESFH net income was Dollars 18.6m, up slightly from Dollars 17.8m for the
same period in 1991. The small increase is attributed to the costs of
financing the acquisition of BESCL.
