FT  14 OCT 92 / International Company News: Kone rises 19.6% to FM240.6m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTOPHER BROWN-HUMES
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   STOCKHOLM
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
KONE, the Finnish elevators group, yesterday reported a 19.6 per cent
increase in pre-tax profits to FM240.6m (Dollars 51.35m) for the first eight
months.
The result compares with FM201.1m in the same 1991 period, and was achieved
on an 11 per cent increase in sales to FM6.2bn. Operating profits before
depreciation rose to FM548.5m from FM499.3m.
Kone said its elevators business increased sales by 10 per cent, giving it a
72 per cent share. Kone Wood lifted sales by more than 50 per cent and
MacGregor-Navire, the marine technology division, by 23 per cent.
New orders during the period were worth FM5.4bn, up 17 per cent from a year
earlier. This took the value of the group's order book at the end of August
to FM6.8bn, up 12.5 per cent.
Kone said it expected a 'satisfactory' development in its financial result
in the final four months, with sales and the value of orders received for
the year as a whole higher than last year's levels. The company is in talks
to acquire a stake in Pragolift, Czechoslovakia's second biggest lift
manufacturer.
