the Cypriot courts to prevent the administrators from gaining control of PPI
assets on the island - Unipac, a packaging company in Famagusta, and Sunzest
Trading, a fruit export concern.
Mr Aziz said he was now discussing an amicable resolution of the dispute.
However he wanted a formal undertaking from the administrators that the
Cypriot companies would not be closed.
'Whether the companies are going to be disposed of, or retained, the
interests of the company and the community must be taken into account,' he
said.
