FT  14 OCT 92 / Construction of toll bridge across River Severn underway
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
CONSTRUCTION of the privately financed Pounds 300m toll bridge across the
River Severn is under way. The bridge is three miles from the existing
bridge, which was built 23 years ago and cannot now handle the traffic
expected to be generated by an improved economy in south Wales.
Construction is being managed by an Anglo-French joint venture of John Laing
and GTM Entrepose, part of a private-sector consortium which is to finance,
build and operate the toll bridge. Other members of the consortium include
Bank of America and Barclays de Zoete Wedd. One thousand workers are
expected to be employed during construction of the bridge, which is due to
be completed in 1996.
