FT  14 OCT 92 / Slight rise in French prices
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
FRENCH consumer prices rose 0.1 per cent in September to give a year-on-year
rise of 2.6 per cent, the Insee statistics institute said yesterday, Reuter
reports. Economists had mostly forecast 0.2 per cent, so the franc, Paris
shares and government bonds all rose on the news. But the response was muted
as the figures showed a continuation of the low inflation trend the
government has maintained with high interest rates and tight spending
policies for several years.
