WITH 165 licensed houses under its management, principally in the west
midlands, north Wales and north west of England, Paramount escaped the worst
of the recession to produce pre-tax profits up 14 per cent to Pounds 403,000
in the year to May 31, compared with Pounds 355,000.
Earnings per share for this USM-quoted company, however, declined from 0.72p
to 0.56p, the equity having been increased by shares issued for
acquisitions. The company is proposing to pay an initial dividend of 0.1p.
Turnover increased from Pounds 5.54m to Pounds 7.64m.
