The ANC demonstration, called to protest at continued exclusion of blacks
from parliament and at government plans to amnesty police and army officers,
was much smaller than expected, with only about 5,000 people taking part.
Organisers had expected 25,000.
South African Communist party veteran Joe Slovo addressed the crowd. 'We
want this place closed down and replaced by a people's parliament. The
people have no vote here. The only parliament you can participate in is the
parliament of the streets,' he said.
