FT  13 OCT 92 / International Company News: US pump plan is cleared
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW BAXTER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
INGERSOLL-RAND and Dresser Industries of the US are going ahead with a plan
to merge virtually all their worldwide pump interests following a decision
by the US Justice Department last month to drop its opposition to the
scheme.
The formation of the joint venture, Ingersoll-Dresser Pump, comes almost 18
months after they originally announced their intention to create the world's
second-biggest pump company after Ebara of Japan.
The move creates a company with about Dollars 900m of sales last year and
8,000 employees.
UK manufacturing facilities at Gateshead, Coleshill and Newark are included
in the deal, but not Dresser's Mono Pump operations.
The merger was cleared by the European Community in January, but the Justice
Department had said the deal was likely to lessen competition substantially
in the US.
