<HEADLINE>
FT  13 OCT 92 / International Company News: Westinghouse hit by Dollars 155m
provision
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By KAREN ZAGOR
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
WESTINGHOUSE Electric, the US conglomerate, yesterday turned in
third-quarter net income of Dollars 14m, or zero cents a share, on
essentially flat revenues of Dollars 3.4bn, reflecting a sharp drop in order
rates and a big provision largely for losses related to an investment in
Phar-Mor.
The Dollars 155m pre-tax third-quarter provision included Dollars 100m for
the Phar-Mor investment, and covered increased credit reserves and valuation
allowances at Westinghouse Financial Services.
A year earlier, Westinghouse had a third-quarter net loss of Dollars 1.48bn,
or Dollars 4.86 a share, including charges of Dollars 1.68bn.
On Wall Street, Westinghouse shares closed unchanged at Dollars 14 5/8 . The
results were released after the close of trading, and the stock was
unavailable for late NYSE trading.
Analysts had expected third-quarter earnings to fall below second-quarter
levels of 35 cents a share, but the erosion was greater than expected.
