<TEXT>
ASTEC, a member of the BSR group, announced that its subsidiary, Beckman
Industrial, had disposed of its instrumentation products division, which
manufactures and markets test instruments, to Wavetek Corporation of San
Diego, California.
Total consideration was Dollars 7.97m (Pounds 4.71m) and in addition, the
purchaser assumed bank borrowings of Dollars 1.21m. Some Dollars 3.5m of the
price was received in cash with the balance payable in ten instalments over
five years.
Net book value of the assets disposed of amounted to Dollars 6.67bn at
December 31 1991.
