<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Six people were arrested and a dozen cars burned when mostly-Arab youths
clashed with riot police for the third night running in Vaulx-en-Velin, the
troubled immigrant suburb of Lyons, Reuter reports.
Youths threw stones at police firing tear gas grenades after a local
resident shot dead a Moroccan-born 18-year-old.
